Carlsberg to Invest in German Plants, Hamburger Abendblatt Says

-- B y   N i k l a s   M a g n u s s o n
-- 
2011-09-22T06:43:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/carlsberg-to-invest-in-german-plants-hamburger-abendblatt-says.html
Carlsberg A/S, the world’s fourth-
largest brewer, will spend 40 million euros ($54 million) on
modernizing its breweries in Hamburg and Luebz in northern
 Germany ,  Hamburger Abendblatt  reported today, citing Frank Massen, head of the Danish company’s operations in Germany.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Niklas Magnusson in Hamburg at 
 nmagnusson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  